@76   = ~Soulfire Ring~
@77   = ~Soulfire gems are as rare as they are beautiful, and hold many magical enchantments. Now whole, the Soulfire Ring is prized for its ability to clear the mind and to regenerate the health of its wearer. This particular Soulfire Ring was made as an engagement ring from <CHARNAME> to his Fey'ri sweetheart, Fade.

STATISTICS

Equipped Abilities:
Wearer regenerates 1 hit point every 6 seconds
Chaotic Commands
Fire Resistance: +10%

Usable by:
Fade~
@78   = ~Soulfire Gem~
@79   = ~Soulfire gems are as rare as they are beautiful, and hold many magical enchantments. Rumoured to hold the trapped spirits of a fire elemental at their hearts, they can be combined with other, flawless gemstones to create potent magical artefacts.~
@80   = ~Uulia'Moor~
@81   = ~This short sword bears the curious name "The Playful Scar", although why it is called that is a mystery to all save the one who named this maleficent blade.  It once belonged to the infamous fey'ri assassin Slythithia. In her time Slythithia was a fighter and sorceress of immense power, and a penchant for cruelty and bloodshed unprecedented even among her own kind. Her nefarious reputation was cemented the day she slaughtered every last resident of a small elven fishing village: men and women, from the oldest man to the youngest babe. Not a soul was spared. Some stories say that Slythithia stumbled upon this village when she was but a child, and her curiosity led her to enter it and explore when she should have ran away. The villagers hurled rocks and rotten vegetables at her, called her a monster and chased her with sticks and spears. Others say that this was just a fanciful tale, and the real reason for the slaughter was simply that Slythithia despised these surface elves, believing them to be pathetic and undeserving of life.

No one knows how or even if Slythithia ever met her end; bards today still sing of the legend of the fey'ri woman who vanished into the mists, never to be seen again. But once a year, when the sky glows red, it is said that she comes back to take the lives of any and all who wander too close to the site of the village she hated to much.

STATISTICS:

Special abillities:
  This weapon is always considered a +4 short sword
  +30% bonus to detect illusion
  5% to stop time for 3 seconds on succesful hit

THAC0:  +4 bonus
Damage:  1D6 +2, +1D4 acid damage
Damage type: piercing
Weight: 3
Speed Factor: 0
Proficiency Type: Short Sword
Type:  1-handed
Requires: 5 Strength
Usable By:
 Fey'ri~
