@84   = ~Olias-Kin Scroll~
@85   = ~This strange parchment has some peculiar marks on it. Even though the signs look as if they were written in blood, you are almost certain that's actually some kind of red ink.~
@86   = ~Fade continued to adventure after leaving <CHARNAME>'s company, but after a few short months, she seemed to disappear. No one knows exactly what became of her, but rumours persist of a pirate queen, one who targets the many slave ships that plague the shores of the remoter areas of Faerun. Tales of her unmerciful stance of killing the crews of ships that insist on trafficking human flesh are now renowned throughout the Realms, as well as her compassionate habit of taking on the former slaves as members of her crew if they so wish. Her identity remains a secret, and the pirates she sails with would never betray her... but the rumour continues that she has hair as red as blood, and fiery gaze and a curious stump, almost as if she once had a tail.~
@87   = ~Fade continued to adventure after leaving <CHARNAME>'s company, but after a few short months, she seemed to disappear. No one knows exactly what became of her, but rumours persist of a pirate queen, one who targets the many slave ships that plague the shores of the remoter areas of Faerun. Tales of her unmerciful stance of killing the crew of ships that insist on trafficking human flesh are now renowned throughout the realms, as well as her compassionate habit of taking on the former slaves as members of her crew if they so wish. Her identity remains a secret, and the pirates she sails with would never betray her... but the rumour continues that she has hair as red as blood, and fiery gaze and a curious stump, almost as if she once had a tail... and that she refuses any man to touch her, as if she is lamenting the loss of some mysterious love, many years ago.~
@88   = ~Fade continued to adventure after leaving <CHARNAME>'s company right up until the birth of her daughter, but a few short months after the birth, she seemed to disappear, abandoning the child to the care of a local temple one stormy night. No one knows exactly what became of her after that, but rumours persist of a pirate queen, one who targets the many slave ships that plague the shores of the remoter areas of Faerun. Tales of her unmerciful stance of killing the crew of ships that insist on trafficking human flesh are now renowned throughout the realms, as well as her compassionate habit of taking on the former slaves as members of her crew if they so wish. Her identity remains a secret, and the pirates she sails with would never betray her... but the rumour continues that she has hair as red as blood, and fiery gaze and a curious stump, almost as if she once had a tail... and that she refuses any man to touch her, as if she is lamenting the loss of some mysterious love, many years ago.~
@89   = ~Once the Bhaalspawn saga was over, Fade and <CHARNAME> decided to travel north. It was on this journey that they made the rather surprising discovery that Fade was with child. After this pleasant revelation, they made the conscious decision not to adventure again, choosing instead to raise their children in the relative peace of a small village, located far to the north of Faerun. After the birth of their twins, <CHARNAME> and his fey'ri love were handfasted and became the appointed protectors of the village they had adopted as their home. Fade at last found the peace within herself to totally accept her own heritage, and whilst outsiders remain suspicious of the hot-tempered tiefling, this does not bother her. "Why should it," she reasons with a smile as she watches her children play outside her small but comfortable cottage, "when I have the love of such a special and extraordinary man?"~
@90   = ~Once the Bhaalspawn saga was over, Fade and <CHARNAME> made the conscious decision not to adventure again, choosing instead to raise their children in the relative peace of a small village, located far to the north of Faerun. After the birth of their twins--Fade's hunch being totally correct --<CHARNAME> and his fey'ri love were handfasted and became the appointed protectors of the village they had adopted as their home. Fade at last found the peace within herself to totally accept her own heritage, and whilst outsiders remain suspicious of the hot-tempered tiefling, this does not bother her. "Why should it," she reasons with a smile as she watches her children play outside her small but comfortable cottage, "when I have the love of such a special and extraordinary man?"~
